title.narrative: CAPACITY TO PROVIDE SERVICES FOR PREVENTION & TREATMENT OF MALNUTRITION

description.narrative: Health facilities, communities and caregivers have improved capacities to provide quality services for and utilize the prevention and treatment of malnutrition., which contributes to Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition In Early Childhood (Covid), Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Safe And Equitable Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Services And Practices, Safe And Equitable Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Services And Practices (Covid), Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Systems And Empowerment Of Communities. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025, parents and children, with a focus on the most vulnerable, have access to equitable, integrated, quality essential health, nutrition and HIV services including during emergencies.

title.narrative: Health facilities, communities and caregivers have improved capacities to provide quality services for and utilize the preventionand treatment of malnutrition.

description.narrative: UNICEF has worked closely with MOH, Department of Water Affairs and NGOs in providing technical and financial support and supplies to improve the capacity of 11 Health facilities to provide quality nutrition services, 35 schools to provide clean water, and 4 communities to promote ODF environment, and 48,596 caregivers to utilize the prevention and treatment of malnutrition through procurement of nutrition supplies; dissemination of information on infant and young child feeding, scaling up access to water in schools and selected communities, promoting handwashing hygiene, generating evidence for better programming, including during the Pandemic and the civil unrest.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/01/2022
